      "class": "top-titled",
      "summary": "This table has three columns and four rows. The first row is a header row, and it labels each column: “Classification,” “Relative ion concentrations,” and “p H at 25 degrees C.” Under the “Classification” column are the following: “acidic,” “neutral,” and “basic.” Under the “Relative ion concentrations” column are the following, “[ H subscript 2 O superscript plus sign ] is greater than [ O H superscript negative sign],” “[ H subscript 2 O superscript plus sign ] equals [ O H superscript negative sign ],” and, “[ H subscript 2 O superscript plus sign ] is less than [ O H superscript negative sing ].” Under the “p H at 25 degrees C” column are the following: “p H is less than 7,” “p H equals 7,” and “p H is greater than 7.”",
